# Predicates:
CategorizedAs(x, y) ::: Machine Learning algorithm x is categorized as y.
SupervisedLearning(x) ::: x is supervised learning.
UnsupervisedLearning(x) ::: x is unsupervised learning.
ReinforcementLearning(x) ::: x is reinforcement learning.
Requires(x, y) ::: x requires y.
LabeledData(x) ::: x is labelled data.
StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(x) ::: x is the state-of-the-art text summarization model.
TrainedWith(x, y) ::: x is trained with y.
MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ::: x is a Machine Learning algorithm.
UsedToTrain(x, y) ::: x is used to train y.
TextSummarizationModel(x) ::: x is a text summarization model.

# Premises:
# General ML algorithm categorization
∀alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) → (SupervisedLearning(alg) ∨ UnsupervisedLearning(alg) ∨ ReinforcementLearning(alg)))
∀alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) → (CategorizedAs(alg, SupervisedLearning) ∨ CategorizedAs(alg, UnsupervisedLearning) ∨ CategorizedAs(alg, ReinforcementLearning)))

# Unsupervised learning characteristics
∀alg (UnsupervisedLearning(alg) → ¬Requires(alg, LabeledData))
∀alg (CategorizedAs(alg, UnsupervisedLearning) → ¬Requires(alg, LabeledData))
∀alg (UnsupervisedLearning(alg) → ¬UsedToTrain(alg, StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel))

# Reinforcement learning characteristics
∀alg (ReinforcementLearning(alg) → ¬UsedToTrain(alg, StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel))
∀alg (CategorizedAs(alg, ReinforcementLearning) → ¬UsedToTrain(alg, StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel))

# Text summarization model requirements
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ∃alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg) ∧ Requires(alg, LabeledData)))
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ∃alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg) ∧ ¬UnsupervisedLearning(alg)))
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ∃alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg) ∧ ¬CategorizedAs(alg, UnsupervisedLearning)))
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ∃alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg) ∧ ¬ReinforcementLearning(alg)))

# Explicit statement about RL not being used for the state-of-the-art model
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ¬∃alg (ReinforcementLearning(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg)))
∀m (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → ¬∃alg (CategorizedAs(alg, ReinforcementLearning) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg)))

# If an algorithm is used to train the state-of-the-art text summarization model, it must be a Machine Learning algorithm.
∀m ∀alg (TrainedWith(m, alg) ∧ StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) → MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg))

# If an algorithm is trained with labelled data, it is either supervised or unsupervised.
∀alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ Requires(alg, LabeledData) → CategorizedAs(alg, SupervisedLearning))
∀alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ Requires(alg, LabeledData) → ¬CategorizedAs(alg, UnsupervisedLearning))
∀alg (MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ Requires(alg, LabeledData) → ¬ReinforcementLearning(alg))

# The state-of-the-art text summarization model is trained with machine learning algorithms.
∃m ∃alg (StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel(m) ∧ MachineLearningAlgorithm(alg) ∧ TrainedWith(m, alg))
# Specific instance for the state-of-the-art model
∃ml (MachineLearningAlgorithm(ml) ∧ TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, ml) ∧ Requires(ml, LabeledData))

# Conclusion:
∀x ((MachineLearningAlgorithm(x) ∧ Requires(x, LabeledData) ∧ TrainedWith(StateOfTheArtTextSummarizationModel, x)) → UnsupervisedLearning(x))
